    <property>
      <content>This is the first release of PhenoTips, an open source software tool for collecting and analyzing phenotypic information for patients with genetic disorders.

Some highlights of the features available in this release are:

* Phenotypic descriptions stored in a standard vocabulary defined by the [[Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)&gt;&gt;http://www.human-phenotype-ontology.org/]]
* The ability to record sets of measurements at different dates, with automatic plotting of measurement values on standard growth charts
* Live search in [[OMIM&gt;&gt;http://www.omim.org/]] and suggestion of disorders that correlate with the current phenotypic profile
* Automatic identification of additional phenotypic features that are associated with those previously selected, that would further improve the depth of the phenotypic description
* The ability to search/filter the patient  database based on different criteria, such as patient age, report date, phenotypes or diseases
* The ability to export the database fully or selectively  in a comma-separated values (CSV) file for external processing
* he ability to export individual patient records as PDF files.
</content>
